<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") -%>

<div class="policy-page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="policy-header">
      <h1><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Last Updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-content">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to HospitalCare Systems Pvt. Ltd. ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website and use our healthcare services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h4>2.1 Personal Information</h4>
        <p>We may collect the following personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Name, address, email address, and phone number</li>
          <li>Date of birth and age</li>
          <li>Medical history and health records</li>
          <li>Insurance information</li>
          <li>Payment and billing information</li>
          <li>Emergency contact details</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-3">2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>IP address and browser type</li>
          <li>Device information and operating system</li>
          <li>Website usage data and analytics</li>
          <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Providing medical care and healthcare services</li>
          <li>Processing appointments and bookings</li>
          <li>Maintaining medical records and patient history</li>
          <li>Processing payments and billing</li>
          <li>Communicating about your health and appointments</li>
          <li>Improving our services and website functionality</li>
          <li>Sending newsletters and updates (with your consent)</li>
          <li>Complying with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Healthcare Providers:</strong> Doctors, specialists, and medical staff involved in your care</li>
          <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third-party vendors who assist in our operations</li>
          <li><strong>Insurance Companies:</strong> For processing claims and coverage verification</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights and safety</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Encryption of sensitive data</li>
          <li>Secure servers and databases</li>
          <li>Regular security audits</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
          <li>Employee training on data protection</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal information</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to legal requirements)</li>
          <li>Opt-out of marketing communications</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for data processing</li>
          <li>File a complaint with data protection authorities</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience on our website. You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings. For more information, please see our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are not directed to individuals under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children without parental consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Changes to Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on our website and updating the "Last Updated" date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@hospitalcare.com</p>
          <p><i class="fas fa-phone"></i> <strong>Phone:</strong> +91 1800-123-4567</p>
          <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> <strong>Address:</strong> Punsia Basti, Banka, Bihar, India</p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-footer">
      <p class="text-center">
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> | 
        <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> | 
        <a href="/contact">Contact Us</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

